{
  "text": "Even with optimal medical management, the mortality in patients with advanced HF is reportedly 40% to 50% at 1 to 2 years. MacIntyre and colleagues demonstrated that mortality among all-comers with CHF at 2 year approaches 45% [CITATION_1] . In the Randomized Evaluation of Mechanical Assistance for the Treatment of Congestive Heart Failure (REMATCH) trial, patients in NYHA IV demonstrated 25% survival at 1 year and 8% survival at 2 years with optimal medical management.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "1738107"
  },
